<section class="min-vh-50 bg-gray alignment">
  <div class="align-items-center pb-5 pt-5">
    <div class="container">
      <h6 class="pt-3">The challenge</h6>
      <h1 class="pb-5">Design and code a Ruby on Rails web app for mobile as a team of four.</h1>
    </div>
      <div class="container">
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-4 pb-3">
            <h6>Background</h6>
            <p>The brief was to create a Ruby on Rails web app from scratch. I pitched the idea for an eco gardening app and my teammates voted to work on it with me.</p>
            <p>We had a day of class-time to hash out the product design, plus evenings and weekends to refine the details, then we coded the app in 8 days.</p>
          </div>
            <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-4 pb-3">
              <h6>The outcome</h6>
              <p>A functioning web app for mobile which provides a simple step-by-step guide for setup, planting, care and harvesting.</p>
              <p>The app shows you which vegetables to plant and harvest and when, depending on the user’s garden specifications.</p>
            </div>
              <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-4 pb-3">
                <h6>Team</h6>
                <p class="pb-3">Patrícia Amaral Nunes, Luís Vaz Pinto, Mariana Saavedra, Louise Hill</p>
                <h6>Role</h6>
                <p class="kill">Concept, UX Design, UI Design</p>
                <p class="pb-3">Front-end and back-end Development</p>
                <h6>Project type</h6>
                <p class="pb-3">Student, @ <u><%= link_to "Le Wagon, Lisbon", "https://www.lewagon.com/lisbon", target: :_blank, class: "desc-link" %></u></p>
              </div>
        </div>
          <h6>Behind the scenes</h6>
          <%= link_to "https://louisehilltech.medium.com/le-wagon-final-project-patched-app-a77fa4647e52", target: :_blank do %>
            <span>
            <h6 class="project-pat pt-3">The full process of creating Patched and final demo
            <%= image_tag("arrow-up-right-blue.svg", alt: "Link arrow", class: "up-arrow") %>
            </h6>
            </span>
            <% end %>
          <%= link_to "https://github.com/lvazpinto/Patched", target: :_blank do %>
            <span class>
            <h6 class="project-pat">The code on Github
            <%= image_tag("arrow-up-right-blue.svg", alt: "Link arrow", class: "up-arrow") %>
            </h6>
            </span>
          <% end %>
      </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section>
  <%= image_tag("patched-tote-bag.png", alt: "Tote bag saying - here for you from planting to plate", class: "w-100") %>
</section>

<section class="min-vh-50 bg-gray alignment">
  <div class="container py-5">
    <div class="row py-5">
      <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-6">
        <h1 class="pb-3">“Most of the gardening blogs and websites did not provide the right information, or communicated it in very complicated terms”</h1>
        <p class="pb-3"><u>
          <%= link_to "plantedwell.com", "https://www.plantedwell.com/gardening-websites-blogs", target: :_blank, class: "desc-link"  %></u>
      </div>
        <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-6">
          <p>I had an afternoon to come up with an app idea so I interviewed a friend. He is an organic gardening enthusiast and opened my eyes to the difficulties of keeping away pests without using harmful chemicals.</p>
          <p>I spoke to a few friends who have recently bought their first house and asked them about their gardens. What jumped out was an enthusiasm for eco-friendly gardening, but uncertainty around how to actually get started. A quick Google highlighted a problem in tracking down clear gardening information for beginners.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="min-vh-50 bg-light-pink">
  <div class="container py-5">
    <div class="row align-items-center py-3 mx-5">
      <%= image_tag("vegetable-selection.png", alt: "Vegetable selection screen", class: "col-12 col-md-6 col-lg-4 py-3") %>
      <%= image_tag("watering-care-screen.png", alt: "Tips on how to water the patch", class: "col-12 col-md-6 col-lg-4 py-3") %>
      <%= image_tag("harvest-screen.png", alt: "Vegetable harvest screen", class: "col-12 col-md-6 col-lg-4 py-3") %>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="min-vh-50 bg-light-pink alignment">
  <div class="container py-5">
    <div class="row py-5">
      <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-6 pb-3">
        <h1 class="pb-1">“Almost 3 million new gardening projects in the last year, nearly half of new gardeners under 45”</h1>
        <p class="quote">
        <u><%= link_to "hortweek.com", "https://www.hortweek.com/new-gardener-estimates-treble-month/retail/article/1693981", target: :_blank, class: "desc-link" %>
        </u>
      </div>
        <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-6 pb-3">
          <p>Research showed a huge boost in gardening during the Corona pandemic, especially amongst under 45s. The <u>
          <%= link_to "HTA Garden Retail Monitor", "https://hta.org.uk/", target: :_blank, class: "desc-link" %>
          </u> found that sales of gardening products were up 34%, 17% and 19% in June, July and August respectively in UK garden centres in 2020, compared to 2019. On average, individual customers were spending 35% more on gardening products. In fact, the <u>
          <%= link_to "Royal Horticultural Society", "https://www.ft.com/content/c3abc0bb-7ade-4ae1-8d2b-d3fa6be53416", target: :_blank, class: "desc-link" %>
          </u> believes gardening is entering a new “golden age”.</p>
          <p>And what about eco-gardening? <u>
          <%= link_to "67% of UK gardeners", "https://www.hortweek.com/covid-19-transformed-gardening-industry-%E2%80%93-so-new-trends/retail/article/1701037", target: :_blank, class: "desc-link" %></u> say they’re eco-conscious and 46% of this group already use organic fertilisers. 
          <u><%= link_to "The 2021 Organic Market Report", "https://www.soilassociation.org/certification/market-research-and-data/the-organic-market-report-2021/", target: :_blank, class: "desc-link" %></u> revealed the highest year-on-year growth in 15 years for the organic market, at +12.6%, with the market now worth £2.79B.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section>
  <%= image_tag("tomatoes-planting.png", alt: "Patched tomato planting screen", class: "w-100") %>
</section>

<section class="min-vh-50 bg-gray alignment">
  <div class="container py-5">
    <div class="row py-5">
      <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-6 pb-3">
        <h1 class="">“120 minute's exposure to nature a week is a key factor in maintaining positive mental health.”</h1>
        <p class="quote pt-3">Dr Alan Kellas, Green Care Lead, Royal College of Psychiatrists</p>
        <p><u>
          <%= link_to "theguardian.com", "https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/may/17/how-lockdown-has-created-veg-growing-revolution-uk-coronavirus", target: :_blank, class: "desc-link" %>
          </u></p>
      </div>
        <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-6">
          <p>The mental health benefits of gardening have been widely documented. A huge study by the <u>
          <%= link_to "University of Exeter", "https://www.exeter.ac.uk/news/research/title_793983_en.html", target: :_blank, class: "desc-link" %></u> on gardens and gardening showed that people who spent time in the garden report better physical and mental health levels than those who do not.</p>
          <p><u>
          <%= link_to "The eco plusses of gardening are also considerable", "https://usgreentechnology.com/environmental-benefits-gardening", target: :_blank, class: "desc-link" %></u>—from supporting beneficial insects and birds, to reducing the carbon footprint of home-grown food, to increasing oxygen in the air.</p>
          <p>As a team we decided on what was feasible to build in the timeframe and focused on growing vegetables so there would be a delicious reward at the end of each growing cycle.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

